726432f-a.title: Queens: Crescent Street - 21st Avenue
726432f-a.text:
Crescent Street, south from 21st Avenue. On the left is
the Seaorest Sanitarium and in the background is the Hellgate
Bridge.
P. L. Sperr  March 23, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS

726431f-a.title: Queens: Crescent Street - 21st Avenue
726431f-a.text:
Crescent Street, east side, between 21st Ave. (left) and Ditmars
Boulevard, showing the William H. Wolcott house in 1873. F.H. Wolcott
removed in 1849 from Flushing to this house. In 1934, it was the
Seacrest Sanitarium, and Dr. Kendrick was the owner.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
